4-36:Every property is selected by the extent to which it is present (a and d: mean, b and c: difference) and only if the amount to which it is present exceeds a certain threshold (depending on the mean and standard deviation over all elements of descriptor space) .
4-37:The implementation of these operators is based on one assumption .
4-38:It is assumed that vector elements measure on interval scale .
4-39:That means, each element expresses that the measured property is "more or less" present ("0": not at all, "M": fully present) .
4-40:This is true for most visual descriptors and all MPEG 7 descriptors .
4-41:A natural origin as it is assumed here ("0") is not needed .
4-42:Introducing p (called discriminance defining parameter) for the thresholds 21 ,εε has the positive consequence that a, b, c, d can then be controlled through a single parameter .
4-43:p is an additional criterion for the behaviour of a distance measure and determines the thresholds used in the operators .
4-44:It expresses how accurate data items are present (quantisation) and consequently, how accurate they should be investigated .
4-45:p can be set by the user or automatically .
