6-35:In Q6, m is 2 M (=0.5) .
6-36:Q3, the Canberra metric, is a normalised form of Q1 .
6-37:Similarly, Q4, Clark's divergence coefficient is a normalised version of Q2 .
6-38:Q6 is a further developed correlation coefficient that is invariant against sign changes .
6-39:This measure is used even though its particular properties are of minor importance for this application domain .
6-40:Finally, Q8 is a measure that takes the differences between adjacent vector elements into account .
6-41:This makes it structurally different from all other measures .
6-42:Obviously, one important distance measure is missing .
6-43:The Mahalanobis distance was not considered, because different descriptors would require different covariance matrices and for some descriptors it is simply impossible to define a covariance matrix .
6-44:If the identity matrix was used in this case, the Mahalanobis distance would degenerate to a Minkowski distance .
6-45:Additionally, the recommended MPEG 7 distances were implemented with the following parameters: In the distance measure of the Color Layout descriptor all weights were set to "1" (as in all other implemented measures) .
6-46:In the distance measure of the Dominant Color descriptor the following parameters were used: 20,1,3.0,7.0 21 ==== dTww α (as recommended) .
6-47:In the Homogeneous Texture descriptor's distance all ( )kα were set to "1" and matching was done rotation and scale invariant .
6-48:Important! Some of the measures presented in this section are distance measures while others are similarity measures .
6-49:For the tests, it is important to notice, that all similarity measures were inverted to distance measures. .
7 TEST SETUP :
7-1:Subsection 4.1 describes the descriptors (including parameters) and the collections (including ground truth information) that were used in the evaluation .
7-2:Subsection 4.2 discusses the evaluation method that was implemented and Subsection 4.3 sketches the test environment used for the evaluation process .
7-3:4.1 Test data For the evaluation eight MPEG 7 descriptors were used .
7-4:All colour descriptors: Color Layout, Color Structure, Dominant Color, Scalable Color, all texture descriptors: Edge Histogram, Homogeneous Texture, Texture Browsing and one shape descriptor: Region based Shape .
7-5:Texture Browsing was used even though the MPEG 7 standard suggests that it is not suitable for retrieval .
7-6:The other basic shape descriptor, Contour based Shape, was not used, because it produces structurally different descriptions that cannot be transformed to data vectors with elements measuring on interval scales .
7-7:The motion descriptors were not used, because they integrate the temporal dimension of visual media and would only be comparable, if the basic colour, texture and shape descriptors would be aggregated over time .
7-8:This was not done .
7-9:Finally, no high level descriptors were used (Localisation, Face Recognition, etc., see Subsection 2.1), because to the author's opinion the behaviour of the basic descriptors on elementary media objects should be evaluated before conclusions on aggregated structures can be drawn .
