8-9:5.1 Best measure per descriptor Figure 2 shows the evaluation results for the first indicator .
8-10:For each descriptor the best measure and the performance of the MPEG 7 recommendation are shown .
8-11:The results are aggregated over the tested datasets .
8-12:On first sight, it becomes clear that the MPEG 7 recommendations are mostly relatively good but never the best .
8-13:For Color Layout the difference between MP7 and the best measure, the Meehl index (Q8), is just 4% and the MPEG 7 measure has a smaller standard deviation .
8-14:The reason why the Meehl index is better may be that this descriptors generates descriptions with elements that have very similar variance .
8-15:Statistical analysis confirmed that (see [6]) .
8-16:For Color Structure, Edge Histogram, Homogeneous Texture, Region based Shape and Scalable Color by far the best measure is pattern difference (P6) .
8-17:Psychological research on human visual perception has revealed that in many situation differences between the query object and a candidate weigh much stronger than common properties .
8-18:The pattern difference measure implements this insight in the most consequent way .
8-19:In the author's opinion, the reason why pattern difference performs so extremely well on many descriptors is due to this fact .
8-20:Additional advantages of pattern difference are that it usually has a very low variance andbecause it is a predicate based measure its discriminance (and cluster structure) can be tuned with parameter p .
8-21:The best measure for Dominant Color turned out to be Clark's Divergence coefficient (Q4) .
8-22:This is a similar measure to pattern difference on the continuous domain .
8-23:The Texture Browsing descriptor is a special problem .
8-24:In the MPEG 7 standard it is recommended to use it exclusively for browsing .
8-25:After testing it for retrieval on various distance measures the author supports this opinion .
8-26:It is very difficult to find a good distance measure for Texture Browsing .
8-27:The proposed Manhattan metric, for example, performs very bad .
8-28:The best measure is predicate based (P7) .
8-29:It works on common properties (a, d) but produces clusters with very high cluster pollution .
8-30:For this descriptor the second indicator is up to eight times higher than for predicate based measures on other descriptors .
8-31:5.2 Best overall measures Figure 3 summarises the results over all descriptors and media collections .
8-32:The diagram should give an indication on the general potential of the investigated distance measures for visual information retrieval .
8-33:It can be seen that the best overall measure is a predicate based one .
8-34:The top performance of pattern difference (P6) proves that the quantisation model is a reasonable method to extend predicate based distance measures on the continuous domain .
8-35:The second best group of measures are the MPEG 7 recommendations, which have a slightly higher mean but a lower standard deviation than pattern difference .
8-36:The third best measure is the Meehl index (Q8), a measure developed for psychological applications but because of its characteristic properties tailormade for certain (homogeneous) descriptors .
8-37:Minkowski metrics are also among the best measures: the average mean and variance of the Manhattan metric (Q1) and the Euclidean metric (Q2) are in the range of Q8 .
8-38:Of course, these measures do not perform particularly well for any of the descriptors .
8-39:Remarkably for a predicate based measure, Tversky's Feature Contrast Model (P1) is also in the group of very good measures (even though it is not among the best) that ends with Q5, the correlation coefficient .
8-40:The other measures either have a significantly higher mean or a very large standard deviation .
8-41:5.3 Other interesting results Distance measures that perform in average worse than others may in certain situations (e.g .
8-42:on specific content) still perform better .
8-43:For Color Layout, for example, Q7 is a very good measure on colour photos .
8-44:It performs as good as Q8 and has a lower standard deviation .
8-45:For artificial images the pattern difference and the Hamming distance produce comparable results as well .
8-46:If colour information is available in media objects, pattern difference performs well on Dominant Color (just 20% worse Q4) and in case of difficult ground truth (group 5, 7, 10) the Meehl index is as strong as P6 .
